<section class="prose-section">
  <div class="prose">
    <div class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2026</div>

    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Lazarus Consulting LLC ("we", "us", "FlightDojo") collects, uses, and shares information about you when you use our website at flightdojo.it.com and related services.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The short version:</strong> We collect the minimum information needed to find and book flights for you. We don't sell your data. We don't track you across the web. You can request deletion at any time.
    </div>

    <h2><span class="num">01.</span>Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>Information you provide</h3>
    <p>When you book a flight or contact us, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Full name and contact details (email, phone)</li>
      <li>Passport or government ID information required by airlines</li>
      <li>Date of birth and nationality</li>
      <li>Payment information (processed by our payment partners — we don't store full card numbers)</li>
      <li>Any communication you send us via email or the contact form</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
    <p>When you visit FlightDojo, we may automatically collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address, browser type, and operating system</li>
      <li>Pages viewed and search queries</li>
      <li>Referring URL and date/time of access</li>
      <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies (see Cookie Policy below)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span class="num">02.</span>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Process flight bookings and communicate with you about reservations</li>
      <li>Provide customer support and respond to your enquiries</li>
      <li>Send transactional emails (booking confirmations, itinerary changes)</li>
      <li>Send marketing emails — only if you've opted in</li>
      <li>Improve our services, detect fraud, and maintain security</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations (tax, anti-fraud, regulatory)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span class="num">03.</span>How We Share Your Information</h2>
    <p>We share your information only when necessary to deliver our service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Airlines and travel partners:</strong> Passenger details required for ticketing</li>
      <li><strong>Payment processors:</strong> To process your booking payments securely</li>
      <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> Hosting, analytics, and support tools bound by confidentiality</li>
      <li><strong>Legal authorities:</strong> Where required by law, court order, or to protect rights and safety</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We <strong>do not sell</strong> your personal information to third parties.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">04.</span>Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
    <p>We use cookies for essential functionality (login state, search context), analytics (understanding traffic patterns), and optional marketing (only if you consent). You can control cookies via your browser settings or our cookie preference centre.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">05.</span>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
      <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Ask us to fix inaccurate information</li>
      <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request that we delete your data, subject to legal retention requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
      <li><strong>Opt-out:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing emails at any time</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:privacy@flightdojo.it.com">privacy@flightdojo.it.com</a>.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">06.</span>Data Security</h2>
    <p>We use industry-standard encryption (TLS 1.3 in transit, AES-256 at rest), access controls, and regular security audits to protect your information. No system is perfectly secure, but we work hard to minimise risk.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">07.</span>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain booking data for 7 years to comply with financial and tax obligations. Marketing data is retained until you unsubscribe. Support correspondence is retained for 2 years. After these periods, data is either deleted or anonymised.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">08.</span>International Transfers</h2>
    <p>FlightDojo is operated from the United States. By using our service, you understand that your information may be processed in the US and other countries where we or our service providers operate. We use Standard Contractual Clauses where required.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">09.</span>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>FlightDojo is not intended for children under 16. We do not knowingly collect information from children. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we'll delete it.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">10.</span>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via email or a prominent notice on our website. The "last updated" date at the top reflects the most recent revision.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">11.</span>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy? Reach our Data Protection Officer at:</p>
    <p><strong>Lazarus Consulting LLC</strong><br/>
    Attn: Privacy<br/>
    1209 Orange Street<br/>
    Wilmington, DE 19801, USA<br/>
    Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@flightdojo.it.com">privacy@flightdojo.it.com</a></p>
